FBIS4-14000 "drnes080_r_94013" FBIS-NES-94-080 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 India Foreign Exchange Reserves Estimated at $14.50 Billion Foreign Exchange Reserves Estimated at $14.50 Billion BK2304103794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 23 Apr 94 BK2304103794 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The government has prepaid $1.13 billion as part of the loan drawn from the International Monetary Fund. A statement of the Reserve Bank of India issued in Bombay yesterday said with this payment the level of the country's foreign exchange reserves stood at $14.50 billion. It may be recalled that the finance minister, Dr. Manmohan Singh, during his budget speech had committed to prepay a part of the IMF loan in view of comfortable foreign exchange reserves position.
